a teenager complained to police that rep joseph 
p kennedy ii pushed him tuesday and struck his head against a car 
after the two were involved in a nearcollision but the youth later 
said he would drop charges 
victor h avila 17 said he would not pursue his complaint 
against kennedy because the congressman had apologized avila said 
he was not hurt avila said he filed assault and battery charges in 
brighton district court tuesday but would drop them wednesday 
mr kennedy came over to my house and he apologized and i 
accepted his apology avila said in a telephone interview tuesday 
evening 
