<TEXT>
the public has glimpsed the nightmarish world of 
domestic violence through hedda nussbaums testimony in the lisa 
steinberg case but experts say more than increased awareness is 
needed to save the lives of children like 6yearold lisa and now 
5yearold jessica cortez 
we were seeing five deaths a day nationally before lisa died 
and five deaths per day since then said dr richard krugman of 
the kempe national center for the prevention of child abuse and 
neglect in denver 
i cant blame the public i dont think the public knows what 
to do said krugman 
lisa steinberg made headlines when she died in november 1987 a 
symbol of a system gone wrong she made frontpage news again last 
week at the trial of joel steinberg the man she knew as daddy 
the man accused of murdering her 
but last wednesday when the brutal beating death in brooklyn of 
5yearold jessica cortez grabbed the headlines away it was the 
same old story only the name had changed 
jessica cortezs mother abigail and the mothers boyfriend 
adrian lopez were unemployed they lived in a cityowned housing 
project in brooklyn on the surface they had nothing in common with 
the steinberg family except that children in their home also were 
battered 
one day after police found lopez standing over jessicas limp 
body they returned to the apartment and found jessicas 9yearold 
halfbrother nicky lebron alvarez quivering in a closet badly 
beaten with 10 bones broken 
family court authorities charged monday that welfare officials 
knew that ms cortez had a history of child neglect but failed to 
tell a judge about it according to a published report the new york 
times said in tuesdays editions that during a 1986 custody hearing 
welfare officials called the woman a good mother even though the 
citys special services for children department had filed a neglect 
petition against her three years earlier 
ninetyfive percent of the american public knows child abuse 
exists thats not the issue anymore said krugman my 
impression is people make some cosmetic changes after rekindled 
awareness of child abuse its like firing a football coach when 
youve got bigger problem than just the coach 
now we need a new kind of public awareness that physical 
abuse of children the lisa steinberg type cases are preventable if 
people want to do something 
the national committee for the prevention of child abuse 
estimated there were 1132 childabuse fatalities in the united 
states last year krugman puts the figure at 2000 to 5000 
there were 225 million official reports of abused children 
nationally in 1987 including 25 percent who were physically abused 
and 14 percent who were sexually abused the committees report 
said jessica cortez fit into both those categories police said 
she also fit into a third category at least 103 children died of 
abuse last year in new york city 
authorities say those numbers arent likely to decline despite 
widespread publicity about child abuse and the steinberg case live 
national television coverage on cable news network a cover story in 
newsweek hours of local tv coverage of ms nussbaums testimony 
but it will have some positive effect they believe 
the steinberg case puts the spotlight on the topic said 
detective joseph ryan coordinator of domestic violence programs for 
the new york city police this case is very important because it 
is that much more detailed and serves to show the dynamics of 
violence in a family situation 
agreed carol digirolamo executive director of the governors 
commission on domestic violence there clearly is some increase in 
awareness 
the deaths of steinberg and jessica also illustrated one of the 
more frightening aspects of child abuse it crosses all lines of 
race economics and geography and domestic violence is rarely 
limited to just one family member experts in the field say 
steinberg was a lawyer ms nussbaum his livein lover was a 
childrens book editor they lived a comfortable existence in a 
historic building in manhattans upscale greenwich village and 
authorities said their two illegally adopted children were 
illtreated 
when lisa was found in a coma nov 2 1987 the other child 
mitchell was sitting in a dirty diaper tethered to a chair and 
drinking spoiled milk ms nussbaum also had been badly battered 
in both the steinberg and cortez cases drugs were apparently 
involved another disturbing trend which has contributed to the 
rising number of child abuse cases 
ms nussbaum has detailed how she and steinberg freebased cocaine 
