tetanus which extends protection to their newborns the report says 
just 25 percent of them are now immunized and tetanus kills more 
than 800000 infants annually 
in 1980 the world health organization launched a campaign to 
reduce the death rate from dehydration caused by diarrhea which 
then claimed the lives of 4 million children annually 
by promoting the use of inexpensive oral rehydration salts a 
simple method for preventing almost all dehydration deaths 112 
nations now are saving the lives of up to 1 million children 
annually the report says 
