the government named institutions in south 
carolina new york and ohio on tuesday to serve as the first three 
regional centers to help funnel scientific advancements to us 
businesses so they can better compete against japanese and other 
trade rivals 
weve been winning the nobel prizes and the japanese have been 
winning the profits said sen ernest f hollings dsc a 
sponsor of the legislation which established the program 
he spoke at a news conference organized by the commerce 
department to announce the choice of the three nonprofit centers 
from among 36 applicants commerce secretary c william verity said 
there will be additional centers but he was uncertain whether three 
or five more will be sought in the next federal budget 
congress has authorized 12 centers altogether but provided money 
only for the first three 12 million for the year ending next sept 
30 to be matched by money from indidividual states and the 
institutions concerned 
the first centers will be at the university of south carolina 
the rensselaer polytechnic institute in troy ny and at the 
cleveland advanced manufacturing program in cleveland 
the centers will help smaller firms take advantage of some of 
the recent and dramatic advances in manufacturing technology 
verity said 
the centers will inform firms in their areas about new 
technology help them evaluate their needs support training for 
their work forces and share their experiences with others 
rensselaer will concentrate on businesses producing parts for the 
auto consumer appliance and electronics industries the south 
carolina technology transfer cooperative will concentrate on metal 
fabrication the cleveland group will deal largely with 
manufacturing 
the program is being administered by the national institute of 
standards and technology a new body succeeding the national bureau 
of standards and established by the trade law president reagan 
signed last august 
in addition to setting standards for industry the new institute 
includes a national computer and telecommunications laboratory a 
national engineering laboratory that specializes in semiconductors 
fiber optics and pipelines and an institute for materials science 
and engineering 
