20 billion a year more to the rich nations than it receives in new 
aid and loans developing nations owe 12 trillion to foreign 
governments private banks and development funds 
its clear that in the 80s private contributions for 
development have doubled while government assistance has declined 
grant said the governments should increase their aid but there 
is also the question of public opinion insisting that they do so 
